, Anton Petrovich went into the front hall, unlocked the door, and Mityushin and Gnushke ushered each other across the threshold.

“Time to go,” said Mityushin, gazing intently at Anton Petrovich. He was wearing his usual pistachio-colored tie, but Gnushke had put on an old frock coat.

“Yes, I am ready,” said Anton Petrovich, “I’ll be right with you.…”

He left them standing in the front hall, rushed into the bedroom, and, in order to gain time, started washing his hands, while 